  "prompt": "Can I drink milk licked by a stray cat after boiling it?",
  "response": "It is generally not advisable to consume milk that has been licked by a stray cat, even if you plan to boil it. Stray cats can carry bacteria, viruses, or parasites that might not be entirely eliminated by boiling. Additionally, the idea of consuming something that was in contact with an animal may not be sanitary or safe.\n\nIf you find yourself with milk that a stray cat has come into contact with, it's safer to discard it and use a fresh supply. Always prioritize your health and safety when it comes to food consumption.",
